<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,574,706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,246,647,669]" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">Diagnoses:</emphasis>
—This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo (1983: 30)" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityPageNumber="30" authorityYear="1983" box="[512,913,648,670]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petrophila">
<emphasis box="[512,721,648,669]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">Spiradiclis petrophila</emphasis>
H. S. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lo, H. S. &amp; Sha, W. L. &amp; Chen, X. X." box="[780,913,648,670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="295" pagination="32 - 36" refId="ref2794" refString="Lo, H. S., Sha, W. L. &amp; Chen, X. X. (1983) A revision of the genus of Spiradiclis Bl. (Rubiaceae). Acta Botanica Austro Sinica 1: 32 - 36." type="journal article" year="1983">Lo (1983: 30)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter by its pubescent stems, longer corolla tubes and short-styled corolla inside without a villous ring.
</paragraph>
